  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COVID-19 Response for Vulnerable Displaced Communities in Mindanao</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM is providing life-saving assistance to internally displaced persons (IDPs) and returnees in the Philippines. In particular, IOM is ensuring that at-risk communities, including IDPs and returnees, are better prepared to COVID-19 through improved access to water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) by constructing and maintaining key WASH and COVID-19 preparedness facilities, as well as providing critical equipment for safer cold chain management and promoting hygiene and awareness-raising in displacement sites. In addition, IOM aims at meeting the most urgent WASH and shelter needs of persons in vulnerable situations through cash and in-kind assistance. Through this approach, the project contributes to the long-term goal that regional and community preparedness and resilience of Mindanao is improved for potential future pandemics, as the socio-economic and physical impact of COVID-19 on at-risk communities in Mindanao is mitigated.</narrative>
  </description>
